==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nutcracker
<hw>Nut"crack`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
instrument for cracking nuts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A European bird
(<spn>Nucifraga caryocatactes</spn>), allied to the magpie and crow. Its
color is dark brown, spotted with white. It feeds on nuts, seeds, and
insects.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The American, or Clarke's, nutcracker
(<spn>Picicorvus Columbianus</spn>) of Western North America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nutgall</ent>⟦br⟧
